### 10. Password Requirements Too Weak
[register/route.ts](file:///Users/mose/Printhub_Antigravity_Audit/printhub_africa/app/api/auth/register/route.ts) — Line 10

```ts
password: z.string().min(8, "At least 8 characters"),
```

Only enforces 8 character minimum. No requirement for uppercase, lowercase, numbers, or special characters. Password `aaaaaaaa` would pass.

**Fix:** Add complexity requirements or use `zxcvbn` for strength scoring.

---

### 11. JWT Callback Queries Database on Every Request for STAFF
[auth.ts](file:///Users/mose/Printhub_Antigravity_Audit/printhub_africa/lib/auth.ts) — Lines 78-83

```ts
if (role === "STAFF" && token.id) {
  const staff = await prisma.staff.findUnique({...});
  token.permissions = staff?.permissions ?? [];
}
```

Every single request from a STAFF user triggers a database query in the JWT callback. With multiple staff users, this becomes a DB bottleneck. The comment says "AUDIT FIX" but the approach is wrong.

**Fix:** Cache permissions with a short TTL (e.g. 5 minutes via Redis or in-memory), or only refresh on explicit permission changes.

---

### 12. Forgot-Password Enables Email Bombing
[forgot-password/route.ts](file:///Users/mose/Printhub_Antigravity_Audit/printhub_africa/app/api/auth/forgot-password/route.ts)

No rate limiting, no cooldown period. An attacker can call this endpoint in a loop with a victim's email, flooding their inbox with reset emails. Not just annoying — it can trigger spam blocks on your Resend sending domain.

---

### 13. No CSRF Protection
The project has **zero CSRF protection**. No CSRF tokens are generated or validated. While NextAuth handles its own CSRF for sign-in, all other API routes (orders, quotes, payments, settings, contact) are unprotected.

---

## 🟡 MEDIUM — Fix Soon

### 14. Hardcoded Secret in Example File
[.env.local.example](file:///Users/mose/Printhub_Antigravity_Audit/printhub_africa/.env.local.example) — Line 13

```
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=lSRuKHzmRDASmnnAbEG0z9eTgM9X4kQ71HiOytEbfM0=
```

A pre-generated secret is in the example file. If anyone copies [.env.local.example](file:///Users/mose/Printhub_Antigravity_Audit/printhub_africa/.env.local.example) to `.env.local` without changing it, every deployment shares the same JWT secret.

**Fix:** Replace with a placeholder like `NEXTAUTH_SECRET=your-secret-here-generate-with-openssl`.

---

### 15. Dockerfile Exposes Hardcoded Database URL
[Dockerfile](file:///Users/mose/Printhub_Antigravity_Audit/printhub_africa/Dockerfile) — Line 18

```dockerfile
ENV DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:password@db:5432/printhub?schema=public"
```

This is baked into a Docker layer. While it's overridden at runtime, the credentials are in the image history.

**Fix:** Use a build-arg or a dummy URL that can't be mistaken for real credentials.

---

### 16. Template Download Links Point to Non-Existent Files
[large-format-printing/page.tsx](file:///Users/mose/Printhub_Antigravity_Audit/printhub_africa/app/(public)/services/large-format-printing/page.tsx) — Lines 636-654

Links to `/templates/rollup-banner.ai`, `/templates/aframe.ai`, `/templates/backdrop.ai`, `/templates/vehicle-wrap-guide.pdf` — none of these files exist in the `public/` directory. Users clicking these get 404s.

