## 🔵 LOW — Improve When Possible

### 22. Google OAuth Configured Without Fallback
[auth.ts](file:///Users/mose/Printhub_Antigravity_Audit/printhub_africa/lib/auth.ts) — Lines 19-22

```ts
GoogleProvider({
  clientId: process.env.GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID ?? "",
  clientSecret: process.env.GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET ?? "",
}),
```

When env vars aren't set, Google OAuth is initialized with empty strings rather than being conditionally excluded. This could lead to confusing errors if a user clicks "Sign in with Google."

---

### 23. Africa's Talking SMS Silently Succeeds Without Credentials
[africas-talking.ts](file:///Users/mose/Printhub_Antigravity_Audit/printhub_africa/lib/africas-talking.ts) — Lines 11-14

```ts
if (!key || !username) {
  console.warn("AT_API_KEY / AT_USERNAME not set; SMS not sent");
  return true; // ← says it worked
}
```

Same pattern as email — claims success when nothing was sent.

---

### 24. Cart Model Stores Items as JSON Blob
[schema.prisma](file:///Users/mose/Printhub_Antigravity_Audit/printhub_africa/prisma/schema.prisma) — Line 793

```prisma
items Json // array of { productId, variantId, quantity, customizations }
```

Cart items are a JSON blob with no referential integrity. If a product is deleted, cart items silently reference non-existent products. No DB-level quantity validation.

---

### 25. Schema Complexity vs Implementation Gap

The Prisma schema is **extensive** (40+ models, 1100+ lines) covering:
- Full asset management (PrinterAsset, MaintenanceLog, MaintenancePartUsed)
- Full inventory system (LFStockItem, ThreeDConsumable, InventoryHardwareItem)
- Full order workflow (ProductionQueue, Machine)
- Corporate accounts, support tickets, newsletters

Many of these models appear to have **little or no API/UI implementation**. This creates maintenance burden and migration complexity for unused features.

---

## Summary Scoreboard

| Category | Score | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| **Security** | 3/10 | No rate limiting, no CSP, unvalidated payment callbacks, no CSRF |
| **Completeness** | 4/10 | 3/4 payment providers stub, S3/Algolia/Sanity stub, template files 404 |
| **Code Quality** | 6/10 | Good use of Zod, proper Prisma patterns, but ESLint suppressed |
| **Test Coverage** | 2/10 | No API tests, no payment tests, minimal coverage |
| **Production Readiness** | 3/10 | No error monitoring, no security headers, email silently fails |
| **Architecture** | 6/10 | Clean route groups, proper middleware, good permission system |

**Overall: Not production-ready.** The security gaps (especially #1 and #2) are exploitable right now if the app is live. The stub services mean core features are broken. Prioritize the 🔴 items immediately.
